            <article class="layout-article" id="firehose-45654095">
        <header class="story-header">
            
            <h1 id="title-45654095"><a href="//yro-beta.slashdot.org/story/13/04/20/1937245/british-womans-twitter-comments-spark-expensive-libel-claims">British Woman's Twitter Comments Spark Expensive Libel Claims</a></h1>
            
                <h4>
                    
                    <a href="//beta.slashdot.org/~timothy" class="author">timothy</a> posted  about a year ago  | from the truth-as-defense dept. 
                    
                </h4>
            
                <span class="topic" id="topic-45654095"> <a href="//beta.slashdot.org/index2.pl?fhfilter=communications" onclick="return addfhfilter('communications');">
            <img src="//c.fsdn.com/s/topics/communications_64.png" width="30px" height="30px" alt="Communications" title="Communications">
        </a></span>
                <a href="//yro-beta.slashdot.org/story/13/04/20/1937245/british-womans-twitter-comments-spark-expensive-libel-claims"><span class="comment-count">303</span></a>
        </header>
	
            
        <div class="elips" data-link="//yro-beta.slashdot.org/story/13/04/20/1937245/british-womans-twitter-comments-spark-expensive-libel-claims">
            <p  id="text-45654095">
                    
                        An anonymous reader writes with this excerpt from the BBC: <i>"A woman who complained about an unpaid &pound;146 invoice is facing a <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-beds-bucks-herts-22224205">libel battle that could cost her more than &pound;100,000</a>. Lesley Kemp, 55, took to Twitter claiming that a company based in the Middle East had failed to pay her promptly for transcription work. Now the firm is suing Mrs Kemp, of Milton Keynes, for defamation, claiming up to &pound;50,000 in damages and a further &pound;70,000 in costs. The company, Resolution Productions, based in Qatar, has yet to comment."</i>
                        
                    
            </p>
        </div>
        <footer class="article-footer">
            
        </footer>
	
